.TH LIBNORN 3 "2026" "norn @PACKAGE_VERSION@" "Library Functions"
.SH NAME
libnorn \- embeddable Mainline DHT, secure sessions, and cluster KV library
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <norn.h>
.fi
.PP
Link with the flags from
.BR pkg-config (1):
.PP
.RS
.EX
cc $(pkg-config --cflags norn) app.c $(pkg-config --libs norn)
.EE
.RE
.PP
or directly:
.B \-lnorn \-lsodium .
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B libnorn
is a C99 library (the foundation under
.BR norn (1)
and
.BR nornd (8))
implementing, in layers:
.IP \(bu 3
.B Mainline DHT \(em
BEP-5 routing and BEP-44 mutable/immutable items
.RI ( norn.h ", " bep44.h ", " kademlia.h ).
.IP \(bu 3
.B Secure sessions and streams \(em
SIGNATURE-authenticated handshakes (ephemeral X25519 signed by the static
Ed25519 identity), reliable multiplexed streams, NAT traversal, rendezvous and
relay
.RI ( norn_session.h ", " stream.h ", " streammux.h ", " norn_nat.h ).
.IP \(bu 3
.B Cluster key-value store \(em
a pure Raft core with PreVote, learners and class-aware candidacy, a replicated
KV with watches and snapshots, and the cluster glue over a pubkey transport
.RI ( norn_raft.h ", " norn_kvstore.h ", " norn_cluster.h ).
.IP \(bu 3
.B Private overlay and tunnelling \(em
fleet bootstrap into a private DHT, and TCP-over-norn forwarding
.RI ( norn_overlay.h ", " norn_forward.h ).
.PP
All cryptography is provided by libsodium
.RI ( crypto.h ).
The DHT and session APIs are asynchronous: drive them from a
.BR poll (2)
loop using
.B norn_get_fd()
and
.BR norn_tick() .
.SH KEY HEADERS
.TP
.B norn.h
DHT client lifecycle, bootstrap, get/put of mutable and immutable items.
.TP
.B norn_session.h
Dial/listen, streams, and the handshake state machine.
.TP
.B norn_cluster.h ", " norn_kvstore.h ", " norn_raft.h
Replicated cluster key-value store and its consensus core.
.TP
.B norn_overlay.h ", " norn_forward.h
Private-overlay bootstrap and stream tunnelling.
.TP
.B crypto.h
Keypairs, signing/verification, and AEAD helpers.
.SH EXAMPLE
.PP
.RS
.EX
#include <norn.h>

keypair_t kp;
crypto_keypair_new(&kp);

norn_config_t cfg = { .version = "myapp/1.0" };
norn_client_t *c = norn_new(kp.public_key, kp.secret_key, &cfg);
norn_bootstrap(c);

int fd = norn_get_fd(c);
for (;;) {
    /* poll(fd, ...) then: */
    norn_tick(c);
}
norn_free(c);
.EE
.RE
.SH THREAD SAFETY
A client/session/cluster handle is not thread-safe; use one per thread or
serialise access. Callbacks run inside
.BR norn_tick ().
.SH API REFERENCE
This page is an overview. The complete, per-function API reference is generated
from the header comments with Doxygen:
.PP
.RS
.EX
make docs        # writes HTML + man3 to docs/api/
.EE
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR norn (1),
.BR nornd (8),
.BR pkg-config (1),
.BR doxygen (1)
.SH AUTHOR
The norn development team.
